OL,3,CMore than 1.5 million older people
OL,4,Ccould face Christmas alone
OL,6,FMore than 1.5 million older people
OL,7,Facross the UK will spend Christmas
OL,8,Falone, according to charity Age UK.
OL,10,FPolling of more than 2,600 people aged
OL,11,F65 and over suggested 11% will eat
OL,12,Fdinner alone on December 25, while 5%
OL,13,Fwill not see or speak to anyone during
OL,14,Fthe entire day.
OL,16,FAge UK says its findings, when
OL,17,Fconsidered in terms of the overall
OL,18,Fpopulation, suggest 1.5 million people
OL,19,Fwill eat alone on Christmas Day.
